g.text: Inland Empire: Your outstretched hand casts a deep shadow on the ground...
Inland Empire: Cold drops of rain fall onto your outstretched hand. A slight tremble passes through it...
Inland Empire: Large flakes of snow fall onto your outstretched hand. A slight tremble passes through it...
Inland Empire: In the back of your head, you feel the rapid beat of anodic music... then it fades away.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant is looking at the spot you were reaching for. "Did you notice something important?"
You: Okay, I'm done with this. [Finish thought.]
Inland Empire: Flakes of snow fall onto your outstretched hand. A slight tremble passes through it...
Kim Kitsuragi: He nods. "Let's get going. We have a case to solve."
Inland Empire: At the back of your head you feel the rapid beat of anodic music... then it fades away.
Endurance: Yes. It's likely triggered by a focal epileptic seizure in your temporal lobe.
Inland Empire: ...and is swept away, out of existence.
You: Did that really happen just now?
You: "Kim, I think I'm seeing Van Eyck posters everywhere now."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Okay. Well. I'm not going to ask who Van Eyck is. I'm just going to assume it's your business and move on, okay?" He raises his collar.
Inland Empire: And so all our lives become but a faded memory, an ephemeral vision of a Van Eyck concert flyer... blink or you'll miss it.
Inland Empire: Your outstretched hand basks in the warm spring sun.
Inland Empire: Things in the night are not what they seem to be...
Shivers: IT HAPPENED ONCE; LONG AGO
Inland Empire: As your hand reaches for the small rectangle of glossy paper, it snaps free from the branch...
Inland Empire: One of the flyers has gotten stuck to the branches of a small brush. The sound of it flapping in the wind is an echo of Van Eyck.
Shivers: A GLIMPSE INTO THE PAST
Endurance: I don't know... probably. I'm not a doctor.
Endurance: Yeah, probably, one day. But not this very minute.
Inland Empire: The shadows play tricks on your mind...
You: "No... I don't think so. It was just a reflection or something. Never mind."
You: "Never mind. Let's get going." [Finish thought.]
You: Oh my god, I'm going to die!
Inland Empire: Cold drops of rain fall onto your outstretched hand. A slight tremble passes through it...
